> We found the following problem with linux kernel 2.2.10 and Solaris
> (Version 2.5 & 2.5.1) NFS (x86). During compiler runs in big projects
> via nfs we had sometimes the case that written data on NFS-Server was
> corrupt. This is of course a really serious effect. It seems so that
> this problem accours since linux kernel 2.2.6. With kernel 2.2.5ac4 the
> problem doesn't accours. Also it is important which OS servs the NFS.
> The combination Linux with kernel 2.2.10 & f.e. Digital Unix 4.0d has no
> problems.
You need to upgrade your Solaris box with the sun provided patches. This is
a Solaris not a Linux bug
